- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a sequent calculus for conditional logics and discusses decidability and space complexity bounds. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a theorem prover for the logics, which is a common topic in AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper mentions the implementation of the theorem prover in SICStus Prolog. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses logics that are used in some machine learning applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents a tool for automated theorem proving, which is relevant to software engineering.
